{
  "page": "Unmasking of Uthero",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Unmasking of Uthero</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> also known as the <b>Uncloaking of Uthero</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf827_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf827-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> was an event in the history of <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a>, in which the city, until then secret to the rest of the nations and realms of the <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">known world</a>, announced its existence. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Unmasking_of_Uthero&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The event is named after <a href=\"/index.php/Uthero_Zalyne\" title=\"Uthero Zalyne\">Uthero Zalyne</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Sealord_of_Braavos\" title=\"Sealord of Braavos\">Sealord of Braavos</a>, who dispatched envoys of the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Bank\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Iron Bank\">Iron Bank</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyria</a> to pay settlements to the grandchildren of the owners of the <a href=\"/index.php/Ship\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ship\">ships</a> Braavos' founders had seized - but not the value of the escaped <a href=\"/index.php/Slave\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slave\">slaves</a>. The <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonlords\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragonlords\">dragonlords</a> turned out to have little interest in the descendants of slaves who had escaped a century before. Several years later, Uthero sent forth ships throughout the world, announcing the existence<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup> of Braavos, and inviting the men of all nations to celebrate the 111th anniversary of the city's founding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf827_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf827-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> However, even after it unveiled itself, Braavos continued to be known as the Secret City,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf26.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf26.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> with its exact location hidden for another two centuries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The anniversary of the Uncloaking is celebrated every year, in a ten day festival of masks and revelry. At midnight on the tenth day, the <a href=\"/index.php/Titan_of_Braavos\" title=\"Titan of Braavos\">Titan of Braavos</a> roars, and all celebrants and revelers remove their masks as one.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf827_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf827-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Unmasking_of_Uthero&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> states the \"existence and location\" of Braavos was made known,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf827_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf827-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> but this contradicts <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> as well as another section of TWOIAF.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf26.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf26.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> See also <a href=\"/index.php/Errata_of_The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire#The_Free_Cities\" title=\"Errata of The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">Errata of <i>The World of Ice &amp; Fire</i></a>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Unmasking_of_Uthero&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_34\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 34\">Chapter 34</a>, Cat Of The Canals.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf827-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf827_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf827_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf827_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf827_2-3\">2.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Beyond the Sunset Kingdom&#58; The Free Cities&#32;(Braavos).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf26.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf26.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf26.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Ancient History&#58; Valyria's Children.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403152849\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.025 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.027 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 872/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 9176/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 3797/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 605/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 13/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 1/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 3136/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   20.536      1 -total\n 73.52%   15.099      9 Template:Ref\n 44.27%    9.092      9 Template:Ref/core\n 24.92%    5.117      1 Template:Refn\n 15.50%    3.184      2 Template:References\n  9.54%    1.960      1 Template:Notes\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:19467-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403152849 and